  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (cd7850b 2023-02-01T00:04:58.420758Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge doc\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nIt seems that \"forge doc\" copies over README.md in repo root over to `docs/src/README.md`.\r\n\r\nNow - I have some diagrams as SVG which I would like for people to be able to see. Sadly this mechanism sabotages any chance of giving it the right URL.\r\n\r\nAnd I can't simply say in root's README.md that docs are available in \"docs/src/README.md\" because it will be copied over.\r\n\r\nThis is super unexpected behavior, my first instinct was to provide some basic info in `README.md` and then fill out all information in `docs/src/README.md`, which then got overwritten to my surprise. Thanks to using local history I was able to recover everything, but that was a close call.",
