    "body": "Which one? The one in the book's directory? Or the one in root's repo? If the repo's root then that already happens.\r\n\r\nI'd say don't copy at all as this will always break relative paths, so it doesn't really make sense to do that.\r\n\r\nAnother approach would be to simply treat `README.md` from repo's root as part of the book, without any copying, but this would highly depend on what you can do with `mdbook` and I'm not sure if that's possible.",
